instructions:
## Set up Lemon Squeezy for Payments and Subscriptions

### 1. Create a Lemon Squeezy store
- Sign up at https://www.lemonsqueezy.com and create a store.
- Add a **Product** (one-time or subscription) and a **Variant** with a price.
- Note the **Variant ID** — needed when creating checkout links.
- Enable **Test Mode** in the dashboard top bar during development. Test payments use no real money.

### 2. Get API credentials
- Dashboard → Account → **API** → generate a new API key.
- Note your **Store ID** (Settings → Store).
- Add to `.env.local`:
  ```
  LEMONSQUEEZY_API_KEY=your_api_key
  LEMONSQUEEZY_STORE_ID=your_store_id
  LEMONSQUEEZY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret
  ```
- Set `LEMONSQUEEZY_WEBHOOK_SECRET` after creating a webhook (step 6).

### 3. Install the SDK
- Install the official Lemon Squeezy JavaScript SDK:
  ```
  npm install @lemonsqueezy/lemonsqueezy-js
  ```

### 4. Initialize the SDK
- Create `src/lib/lemonsqueezy.ts`:
  ```
  import { lemonSqueezySetup } from '@lemonsqueezy/lemonsqueezy-js';

  lemonSqueezySetup({
    apiKey: process.env.LEMONSQUEEZY_API_KEY!,
    onError: (error) => console.error('Lemon Squeezy error:', error),
  });

  export * from '@lemonsqueezy/lemonsqueezy-js';
  ```
- Call `lemonSqueezySetup` once (server-side only) before using any other SDK function.
- Import all SDK functions from this file to guarantee setup runs first.

### 5. Create a checkout link (Server Action or API route)
- Dynamically create a checkout URL for a specific variant:
  ```
  import { createCheckout } from '@/lib/lemonsqueezy';

  export async function createCheckoutUrl(variantId: number, userId: string, email: string) {
    const { data, error } = await createCheckout(
      process.env.LEMONSQUEEZY_STORE_ID!,
      String(variantId),
      {
        checkoutData: {
          email,
          custom: { user_id: userId },  // returned in every webhook payload
        },
        productOptions: {
          redirectUrl: `${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL}/dashboard?success=true`,
          receiptButtonText: 'Go to dashboard',
        },
      }
    );

    if (error) throw new Error(error.message);
    return data?.data.attributes.url;
  }
  ```
- The `custom` object is included in all webhook payloads — always pass `user_id` so you can link payments to users.

### 6. Checkout overlay (frontend)
- Add the Lemon Squeezy overlay script to `app/layout.tsx`:
  ```
  import Script from 'next/script';
  <Script src="https://app.lemonsqueezy.com/js/lemon.js" defer />
  ```
- Create a client button component:
  ```
  'use client';
  export function BuyButton({ checkoutUrl }: { checkoutUrl: string }) {
    function open(e: React.MouseEvent) {
      e.preventDefault();
      (window as any).LemonSqueezy?.Url?.Open(checkoutUrl);
    }
    return (
      <button onClick={open} className="lemonsqueezy-button">
        Buy Now
      </button>
    );
  }
  ```
- `LemonSqueezy.Url.Open()` opens checkout in a modal overlay — users never leave your site.

### 7. Webhooks
- In Lemon Squeezy dashboard → Settings → **Webhooks** → Add webhook:
  - URL: `https://yourapp.com/api/webhooks/lemonsqueezy`
  - Events: `order_created`, `subscription_created`, `subscription_updated`, `subscription_cancelled`
  - Copy the **signing secret** → add to `LEMONSQUEEZY_WEBHOOK_SECRET`.
- Create `src/app/api/webhooks/lemonsqueezy/route.ts`:
  ```
  import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';
  import crypto from 'crypto';

  export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
    const rawBody = await request.text();  // must read as text BEFORE parsing
    const signature = request.headers.get('x-signature');

    const digest = crypto
      .createHmac('sha256', process.env.LEMONSQUEEZY_WEBHOOK_SECRET!)
      .update(rawBody)
      .digest('hex');

    if (digest !== signature) {
      return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Invalid signature' }, { status: 401 });
    }

    const payload = JSON.parse(rawBody);
    const eventType: string = payload.meta.event_name;
    const userId: string = payload.meta.custom_data?.user_id;

    switch (eventType) {
      case 'order_created':
        await grantAccess(userId, payload.data.attributes);
        break;
      case 'subscription_created':
      case 'subscription_updated':
        await updateSubscription(userId, payload.data.id, payload.data.attributes);
        break;
      case 'subscription_cancelled':
        await cancelSubscription(userId);
        break;
    }

    return NextResponse.json({ received: true });
  }
  ```

### 8. Customer billing portal
- Let subscribers manage their plan via the Lemon Squeezy customer portal.
- Store `subscription_id` from the `subscription_created` webhook payload in your database.
- Fetch the portal URL:
  ```
  import { getSubscription } from '@/lib/lemonsqueezy';

  const { data } = await getSubscription(subscriptionId);
  const portalUrl = data?.data.attributes.urls.customer_portal;
  redirect(portalUrl);
  ```

### 9. License key verification (for desktop/API products)
- Activate on first use:
  ```
  import { activateLicense } from '@/lib/lemonsqueezy';
  await activateLicense(licenseKey, 'my-app-instance');
  ```
- Validate on every protected request:
  ```
  import { validateLicense } from '@/lib/lemonsqueezy';
  const { data, error } = await validateLicense(licenseKey);
  if (error || data?.data.attributes.status !== 'active') {
    throw new Error('Invalid or expired license');
  }
  ```

### 10. Test the integration
- In Test Mode, use card `4242 4242 4242 4242`, any future expiry, any CVC.
- Trigger test webhooks: Lemon Squeezy dashboard → Webhooks → **Send test event**.
- Verify `userId` arrives in `payload.meta.custom_data.user_id`.
- Switch to **Live Mode** before going to production — API keys change, update all production env vars.

### Common errors & fixes
- **'Invalid API key'** → Key regenerated or wrong store. Regenerate from Account → API.
- **Webhook signature mismatch** → `request.json()` was called before `request.text()`, consuming the body stream. Always read raw body first.
- **`custom_data` is undefined in webhook** → `checkoutData.custom` was not set in `createCheckout`. Always pass the `custom` object.
- **Checkout overlay not opening** → `lemon.js` not loaded (missing `<Script>` tag) or called before DOM ready. Add `defer` to the script tag.
- **Test orders not in Live dashboard** → Test and Live environments are separate. Use the mode toggle.
- **Portal URL is null** → Subscription ID is wrong, or the product is not a subscription variant. Log `payload.data.id` from the webhook to verify.
- **SDK functions undefined** → `lemonSqueezySetup` was not called. Import all SDK functions from `@/lib/lemonsqueezy` (which calls setup) not directly from the package.

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT call `request.json()` before `request.text()` in the webhook handler — it consumes the stream and breaks signature verification.
- Do NOT expose `LEMONSQUEEZY_API_KEY` to the browser — never prefix it with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`.
- Do NOT skip `custom: { user_id }` in checkout — without it you cannot link payments to users in your webhook handler.
- Do NOT rely on the checkout redirect URL for order fulfillment — users can close the tab. Always fulfill via webhooks.
- Do NOT forget to switch from Test Mode to Live Mode before launch — keys and checkout URLs differ between modes.
- Do NOT call Lemon Squeezy SDK functions from Client Components — all SDK operations are server-only.
- Do NOT hardcode variant IDs in the frontend — store them as environment variables for easy plan management.
